Some Nigerians living in Spain has on Friday, attacked the Transportation Minister, Rotimi Amaechi, who was on a national assignment. Amaechi, who disclosed this on his twitter handle said he was attacked by a few misguided Nigerians while on national assignment at a climate change event in Madrid, Spain. I’ve never collected one kobo as pension from Rivers – Amaechi He wrote, “Some minutes ago, I was attacked by a few misguided Nigerians while on national assignment at a climate change event in Madrid, Spain.” “They were quickly repelled by the Spanish police before they could do any harm. I am fine. I was not hurt. Thanks for your support & prayers.” Some minutes ago, I was attacked by a few misguided Nigerians while on national assignment at a climate change event in Madrid, Spain. They were quickly repelled by the Spanish police before they could do any harm. I am fine. I was not hurt. Thanks for your support & prayers.